NBC SPORTS PRIVACY NOTICE
NBC Sports takes your privacy seriously. This statement describes what information we collect on this NBC Sports portal, how we use it, who we share it with, and how you can contact us if you have any questions or concerns.
1. What Kind of Information Do We Collect?
NBC Sport collects, stores and uses various types of information about you including information about your device, including but not limited to cookies, unique identifiers, geographic information, and analytics data. We also collect personal information about you which may include, but is not limited to:
Contact information
, such as name, home and business addresses, telephone numbers, email addresses, and emergency contact information.
Demographic information
, such as gender, age, race / ethnicity (optional).
Financial information
, such as social security number, tax related information, banking information, and other financial information related to employment.
Identification information
, such as copies of “right to work” documentation (including passports, and visas), citizenship, photographs, other identification documentation (including driver’s license, social security card, birth certificate etc.) and information related to benefit administration if applicable.
Career/employment administration information
, such as job titles, work history, references, start and end dates, work location, and preferences (e.g. mobility), absence and leave (including leave due to sickness/injury, annual leave, emergency leave records, memberships, and information related to benefit administration if applicable.
CCTV footage
and other information obtained through electronic means, such as security pass records.
Veteran Status
(optional)
Information about
business travel and expenses
.
Specifically in relation to any event deemed a pandemic by governmental or health organizations (e.g. COVID-19), we may use information about your
potential exposure, potential symptoms, pre-existing conditions or heightened health risk factors, diagnoses or information about your immunity status.
2. How Will We Use Your Information?
Your information is used for:
Managing and administering your account registrations and applications.
Communicating with you
about the process and to send you news about NBC Sports events and opportunities that might be of interest to you (you can unsubscribe from these alerts at any time).
Providing you with benefits and services.
Administration and HR management including processing payroll, benefits and other compensation.
Keeping records relating to our NBC Sports events.
Security management, such as to ensure network and information security, monitoring (including through use of CCTV) and controlling access to NBC Sports premises.
Reporting and data analytics to help us visualize and monitor the effectiveness of our processes, identify trends, improve our processes and allocate our resources effectively.
We will use information about leaves of absence; your physical or mental health or disability status to ensure your health and safety in the workplace and to assess your fitness to work, to provide, where applicable, appropriate workplace adjustments, to monitor and manage sickness absence and to administer benefits; all to comply with (and exercise rights under) employment and other laws and our contractual obligations, to protect your vital interests, and for payroll calculations.
We will use information that you voluntarily provide about your disability, race, national or ethnic origin (as well as information that you provide about gender and age), to ensure meaningful equal opportunity and diversity and inclusion monitoring and reporting.
Protecting our business interests and legal rights, including use in connection with legal claims (including disclosure of such information in connection with legal process or litigation), in connection with the sale, purchase or merger of a business; and for compliance, regulatory, auditing, investigative and compliance reporting purposes.
Specifically in relation to any event deemed a pandemic by governmental or health organizations (e.g. COVID-19), we may use information about your potential exposure, potential symptoms, pre-existing conditions or heightened health risk factors, diagnoses or information about your immunity status to take steps to protect your health and safety and that of our workforce, and to conduct workforce planning, management and operational activities. E.g. we might ask you to go (or stay) home, ask you about recent interactions with colleagues, arrange for you to be tested for Covid-19 (if appropriate), and conduct data analysis to monitor and manage the impact of Covid-19 on our business operations.
3. Who Could My Information Be Disclosed To?
Within NBC Sports:
Your Information will be accessible to authorized NBC Sports personnel for onboarding and payroll purposes. This includes your manager, your HR representative and cross-business NBCUniversal functions such as HR Operations, Technology, Corporate Legal and Payroll, and the Comcast Benefits team in relation to benefits administration, if applicable.
Third Parties:
NBC Sports may use or partner with third parties including service providers to assist with the collection, processing and validation of personal information, such as compensation and benefits providers, technology service providers, corporate card issuers, travel management providers, HR management and administration suppliers (e.g. survey providers, employee recognition providers), and the provider of our ethics hotline.
NBC Sports will only disclose personal information to third parties other than as described above when required to do so by law, regulation or legal process, in response to a legitimate request for assistance by the police or other law enforcement agency or to seek legal advice from NBC Sports' external lawyers or in connection with litigation with a third party.
4. How Do We Protect It?
We maintain procedural, technical, and physical safeguards to help protect against the loss, misuse or unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction of personal information. These safeguards vary depending upon the sensitivity of the information we collect and store. Please be aware that no security solutions are infallible.
5. Account Profile Information
When you register for an account, we will ask you to create a password. Some of the information you provide to us will be associated with your account profile. You are able to update your information at any time by contacting your manager or human resources. Please note that additional supporting documentation may be required.
6. Your Rights
If you have a concern about how we have used your personal information, please contact your HR representative in writing. For your privacy and safety, we may adopt reasonable measures to confirm your identity before processing your request.
If you have any questions about this privacy notice or how we handle your personal information, please contact our Privacy department at
privacy.operations@nbcuni.com
.
7. Contacting Us
You may contact us at the following address:
NBC Sports Group
1 Blachley Road
Stamford, CT 06902
Attn: Remotes Onboarding, HR Portal
